     1	//! 0.7.2 PR-7 — perf regression detector.
     2	//!
     3	//! Reads the append-only `dev/perf-history/` store (one JSON file per
     4	//! canonical / release-time run), groups records by `(ac_id, n)`, and flags
     5	//! the single most-recent run in each group against the rolling median of
     6	//! the prior runs in that group. Tier-aware: `n` is part of the grouping key
     7	//! so a 10k-tier run is never compared against a 100k/1M-tier run, and the
     8	//! real-corpus (N=7667) group is distinct from the synthetic N=10000 group.
     9	//!
    10	//! Design + thresholds + provenance:
    11	//! `dev/design/perf-regression-detection.md`.
    12	//!
    13	//! ## Append-only invariant
    14	//!
    15	//! This binary **only reads** the history directory — it never writes,
    16	//! mutates, or deletes any file. CI (or a human, for the locally-measured
    17	//! AC-013/AC-013b/AC-019 numbers) writes new files. A regression is a new
    18	//! file whose numbers this bin flags, not an edit to an old file.
    19	//!
    20	//! ## Record schema (one JSON object per file)
    21	//!
    22	//! ```json
    23	//! {
    24	//!   "commit_sha": "c893d8b0",
    25	//!   "ac_id": "AC-013",
    26	//!   "n": 10000,
    27	//!   "p50_ms": 36.0,
    28	//!   "p99_ms": 49.0,
    29	//!   "recall": 0.937,
    30	//!   "timestamp": "2026-06-01T07:23:39Z"
    31	//! }
    32	//! ```
    33	//!
    34	//! - `commit_sha`, `ac_id`, `n`, `timestamp` are required.
    35	//! - `p50_ms` / `p99_ms` are omitted for recall-only ACs (AC-013b).
    36	//! - `recall` is omitted/null for latency-only ACs (AC-012, AC-019).
    37	//! - A record MUST carry at least one comparable metric (a latency pair or a
    38	//!   recall value), else it is malformed (exit 2).
    39	//! - **Unknown fields are ignored, not rejected** (forward-extensible).
    40	//!
    41	//! ## Exit codes
    42	//!
    43	//! - `0` = no regression flagged (includes all-insufficient-history).
    44	//! - `1` = at least one group flagged a regression.
    45	//! - `2` = data missing / malformed (directory absent, unreadable/invalid
    46	//!   JSON, record with no comparable metric).
