1. BLOCK: `parse_rfc3339_epoch` is still not a strict RFC3339 validator, so pass-1 finding #2 is only partially fixed. In [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:136), the parser checks only `month in 1..=12` and `day in 1..=31`, then feeds the values into `days_from_civil`; that silently normalizes impossible dates like `2026-02-31`. In [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:147), the zone offset parser never bounds offset hour/minute, so malformed offsets like `+24:99` are accepted. In [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:157), everything after `.` is discarded without validating that the fractional suffix is digits, so malformed timestamps such as `...:27.badZ` would also be accepted. That contradicts the “strict RFC3339” guarantee in [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:123) and [perf-regression-detection.md](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/dev/design/perf-regression-detection.md:124). The new fixture/test only exercises a missing-`T` form ([AC-013-feedface-10000.json](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/fixtures/malformed-timestamp/AC-013-feedface-10000.json:1), [perf_regression_check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/perf_regression_check.rs:117)), so this gap is not covered. Precise fix: validate month-specific day counts with leap-year handling, bound offset hour/minute, require fractional seconds to be digits-only, and add tests for those cases.

The other two pass-1 blockers do look fixed: the committed `AC-013b@10000` arc now sorts bug → fix → dense → ship by real git chronology, the committed store is clean with only that group having sufficient history, and the workflow now reports through `$GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY` with `contents: read` only ([perf-canonical.yml](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/.github/workflows/perf-canonical.yml:71), [perf-canonical.yml](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/.github/workflows/perf-canonical.yml:171)). I also verified the current prebuilt test binary and checker binary in `target/debug`/`target/debug/deps` for the committed fixtures because fresh `cargo test` was blocked by the read-only sandbox.

